Criminal proceedings against businessman Jimi Wanjigi and his father Maina Wanjigi will not continue until their applications to stop the case are heard and determined, a Nyeri court heard yesterday. Their lawyer told Chief Magistrate Wendy Kagendo that the suspension of the proceedings had already been extended by High Court judges John Mativo and Pauline Nyamweya. ALSO READ:

